[2013-06-08T03:41-04:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    "मी कल्पेश शिर्के मूळचा मुंबई मधील गोरेगाव चा. तुमच पेज मला खूप आवडल आणि काही वर्षापूर्वी माझ्याबरोबर घडलेली एक घटना आज येथे शेर करावीशी वाटली..
     .
     .मी तेव्हा 13 वर्षाचा होतो . आणि गावा वरुन आत्ये भावच्या लग्नाची पत्रिका नुकतीच आली होती.मे महिना होता. आणि शाळेला भरपूर सुट्ट्या सुधा होत्या . त्यात गावाला जाण म्हणजे आनंदाची पर्वणीच माझ्यासाठी. एकदाचे आम्ही गावाला येऊन पोहचलो . लग्न असल्यामुळे सगळी भावंड अगोदरच गावाला आली होती. आणि तेव्हा मी सगळ्यात लहान असल्यामुळे माझे लाड होत असत......
    
     आत्याच गाव चिपळूण पासून सुमारे 12 की. मी अंतरावर आहे गावाच नाव केळने. गाव डोंगराच्या मधे असल्याने निसर्गाने जणू सगळी सुंदरता त्यात भरली होती. आत्ता मैं स्टोरी ला सुरवात करतो.......
    
     तो लग्नाच्या आधीचा म्हणजे हळदिचा दिवस होता घरात लग्न असल्यामुळे सगळे वेगवेगळ्या कामात व्यस्त होते. सगळ्या भावंडानी काम वाटून घेतली होती. मी आणि माझी ताई रेखा आमच्या दोघांवर पाणी भरण्याचे काम सोपवण्यात आले. पाणी भरण्या साठी विहरीवर जाव लागत असे. ती विहीर घरा पासून 5 मिनटांच्या अंतरावर होती. आणि ती विहीर जमिनीला लागून होती म्हणजे तिच्या बाजूला सुरक्षा कड नव्हती . त्या मुळे लहान मूलाना सहसा तिथे जाऊ दिले जात नव्हते. विहीर तशी खोल नव्हती 4 ते 5 फुट पाणी असेल त्यात.आणि विहरीच्या बाजूला एक मोठे चिंचेचे झाड होते..
    
     तर झाल अस की रेखा ताई आणि मी दोघ निघालो पाणी भरण्यासाठी दुपारचे 12. ते 12.30 वाजले असतील काही वेळात पोहचलो विहरी जवळ तेवा तिथे कोणीच नव्हते. आमच्या गप्पा चालू होत्या ताई विहरीतून पाणी काढून हंडा भरत होती आणि मी त्या विहरीत वाकून बघत होतो. विहरीत समोरच्या चिंचेची पान पडत होती. सगळ वातावरण एकदम शांत होत . तेवढ्यात ताई म्हणाली तुला माहीत आहे का कल्पेश या झाडावर जखिण राहते अस म्हणतात. ते ऐकून मी ताई ला चिडवत म्हणालो राहते ना मग बोलव मी नाही घाबरत कोणाला . तर मस्करी म्हणून ताई जोरात बोलली ए जखिणी ये आणि धर आमच्या कल्पेश ला. ती हे बोलताच आम्ही दोघे पण हसायला लागलो आणि ताई ने भरलेला एक हंडा माझ्या डोक्यावर दिला आणि म्हणाली हो पुढे आणि ती तिचा हंडा उचलू लागली तसा मी घरच्या दिशेने वळलो. मी 4 ते 5 पावल टाकली असतील अचानक धाड असा मोठा आवाज झाला.. अचानक अंगातून एक शीरशिरी उठली . मी मागे वळून पहिले तर ताई कुठेच दिसत नव्हती. मी घाबरलो पाय थरथारू लागले पण ताई चा विचार करून हिंमत केली आणि विहारी जवळ गेलो आणि खाली डोकवून पहिले. आणि जे पहिले ते कधीच विसरू शकत नाही
    
     ताई विहरित उभी होती पूर्ण ओले केस डोळे लाल लाल झलेले होते आणि एक विचित्र हास्य तिच्या तोंडावर होते आणि सारखी मान वाकडी तीकडी करत होती तेव्हा
     आणि अचानक तिने मला आवाज दिला की ये खाली ये मी तुला घ्यायला आली आहे . हे ऐकून माझी टरकलि . अंगात जेवढी शक्ति होती तेवढी एकवाटून मी घरच्या दिशेने पाळायला लागलो. धापा टाकत अंगणात येऊन पडलो माझी ती गत बघून सगळे माझ्या दिशेने धावत आले मला उचलले आणि पाणी पाजले मी बोललो ताई बावडीत पडली आहे हे ऐकून मामा , आणि दोन चार मोठी मंडळी विहरीच्या दिशेने धावले. अर्ध्या तासाने ते सगळे लोक ताई ला पकडून घेऊन आले . ती जोर जोरात किंचाळत होती. ओरडत होती. की मला तो पाहिजे ते ऐकून मी अजुन घाबरलो मोठ्या मंडळीनी लगेच गावातील एका मंत्रीक बाबाना बोलावले . आणि ताई ला त्यांच्या समोर बसवले काही मंत्र उच्चारण केले आणि ताई ला विचारले कोण आहेस तू आणि का या मुलीच्या मागे लागली आहेस. तेव्हा ती जोरजोरात हसायला लागली आणि म्हणाली मी चिंचेची शेंद्री जखिण आहे . हिने मला बोलवल आहे. त्या मुलाला घेऊन जाण्यासाठी आता मी या दोघाना पण सोबत घेऊन जाणार. तेव्हा सगळेच घाबरले मग मंत्रिकने काही अजुन मंत्र म्हटले आणि तिला विचारल या मुलांकडून चुक झाली त्याना क्षमा कर आणि त्या बदल्यात तुला हव ते देतो . तेव्हा ती म्हणाली नाही मला अजुन काहीच नको मला हे दोघ हवे आहेत माझी मस्करी करतात याना मी घेऊन जाणार तेव्हा मंत्रिकाने काही मंत्र म्हटला आणि त्याच्या पिशवीतून एक रखेची पुडी बाहेर काढली आणि ती तिच्या कपाळाला लावली तशी ती रडू लागली तिला त्रास होऊ लागला मंत्रीक पुन्हा म्हणाला जातेस की नाही तेव्हा ती म्हणाली मला हिरवी साडी आणि मांसाहाराच जेवण पाहिजे तरच मी याना सोडेन . मंत्रिकने ते कबूल केल द्यायच आणि मामाना एक साडी आणि मटनाच ताट घेऊन बावडी जवळ ठेवायला संगितल ते सर्व होई पर्यंत मंत्रिकच मंत्र बोलन आणि ताई च माझया कडे रागाने बघन चालूच राहील . मामा सगळ्या विधी करून घरी आला तसा मंत्रिकने ताई कडे बघितल आणि ओरडला जेया आता तुझी मागणी पूर्ण झाली आहे. आणि परत तो अंगारा काही मंत्र बोलून तिच्या आणि माझ्या कपाळाला लावला तसा ताई शांत झाली आणि पडली.......
    
     मंत्रिकने एक दोरा आमच्या हाताला बांधला आणि निघून गेला. सगळ शांत झाले थोड्या वेळाने रेखा ताई उठली आणि म्हणाली अरे आपण इथे कसे आपण तर पाणी आणायला गेलो होतो ना ......... तेव्हा मामा बोलले हो पण तुला चक्कर आली म्हणून तुला घरी आणून झोपवले पाणी भरून झाल आता .... तिकडे जायाच नाही दुसर्या दिवशी लग्न आटोपल तसेच आम्ही मुंबई ची गाडी पकडली कारण अजुन काही विपरीत होऊ नये म्हणून आणि त्या दिवसाला आज 12 वर्ष झाली मी परत कधीच अत्याच्या गावाला गेलो नाही ....

    Dear Facebook Members,
    
    Facebook is recently becoming very overpopulated. There have been many members complaining that Facebook is becoming very slow. Records show that the reason is that there are many active Facebook members and, on the other side, many new Facebook membe..................rs.

    Send this message to all your friends and to show me that your still active and you will not be deleted.
    
    Founder of Facebook,
    
    Mark Zuckenberg

    ऋणानुबंधांच्या जिथून पडल्या गाठी
    भेटीत तृष्टता मोठी
    
    त्या कातरवेळा थरथरती कधि अधरी
    त्या तिन्हीसांजा त्या आठवणी त्या प्रहरी
    कितिदा आलो, गेलो, जमलो
    रुसण्यावाचुनि परस्परांच्या कधी न घडल्या गोष्टी
    
    कधि तिने मनोरम रुसणे
    रुसण्यात उगीच ते हसणे
    म्हणून ते मनोहर रुसणे
    हसणे, रुसणे, रुसणे, हसणे
    हसण्यावरती रुसण्यासाठी, जन्मजन्मिच्या गाठी
    
    कधि जवळ सुखाने बसलो
    दुःखात सुखाला हसलो
    कधि गहिवरलो, कधि धुसफुसलो
    सागरतीरी आठवणींनी वाळूत मारल्या रेघा
    जल्मासाठी जल्म जल्मलो, जल्मात जमली ना गट्टी

[2013-05-16T11:30-04:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    I still remember how I found my true home..Where I really belonged..
    I was fourteen and some creepy looking monster with a single eye in the middle of his forehead had come..
    I recognised him..
    it was cyclops..
    Striaght from the books I used to read!!
    The one who eats satyrs for dinners..
    Just like one Odysseus had tricked centuries ago..
    Dont ask me how I had known that..
    I was big fan of all the mythological books since I was child and My foster mom had a large stock of them..
    I had seen monsters before but not as nasty as it!!
    not as creepy as him and definately not d one who could defeat my MOM..
    I used to think I was going mad when I could see characters from books I read..
    I had seen Fury once..
    It had attacked our home when I was 13..
    My Mom had fought it and reduced it to vapours..
    she had told me it was all my imagination but now I knew the truth..
    now I knew how she had died Hero..
    
    	Now I know why she has adopted ADHD and dyslexic child from orphange.She was just like me.

[2015-09-13T11:54-04:00] Ashwin Kapre: 

    check this out
    num_cities=int(input(""))
    num_tra=int(input(""))
    N=0
    fav_city=[]
    award=[]
    award_t=[]
    for i in range(0,num_cities):#creting list for awards
        award_t[i:i]=[1]
    for i in range(0,num_cities):#creting list for awards
        award[i:i]=[0]
    while(N<num_tra):
        fav_city[N:N]=[int(input(""))]
        N=N+1
    for i in range(1,num_cities+1):#n number of times visits
        for j in range(1,num_cities+1): #checking divisibliy for each city
            if j%i==0:
                for k in range(0,num_tra):#every traverl
                    if fav_city[k]==j:
                        if award_t[k]==1:  
                            award[j-1]=award[j-1]+1
                            award_t[k]=0
                        else:
                            award_t[k]=1
                            award[j-1]=award[j-1]-1
    N=0
    for i in award:
        if award[N]>0:
            print(N+1,award[N])
        N=N+1

[2015-09-13T11:56-04:00] Ashwin Kapre: 

    Problem Statement
    
    Some time back Anujay decided that competitive programming is not the only thing that is important for him. So now he visits gym every day, because he wants to gain strength and be in good shape. 
    
    Anujay is free to visit the gym during next N days. The days are numbered from 1 to N. His coaches, Olya and Dima, want to make a plan for his trainings so that Anujay would gain the maximal possible amount of strength. 
    
    After googling for some time, they come to know about M exercises. They have to choose a subset of exercises, according to the following constraint, so that total strength gained will be maximal. 
    
    ith exercise is represented by a set of five integers: Li,Ri,Di,Ci,Si. So if ith exercise is opted, it has to be started on Lith day and has to be repeated daily. This repetition has to go on till EndDay day, where EndDay∈[Ri,Di]. When this is done, Si+Ci×(EndDay−Li+1) units of strength is gained. It is not allowed to do more than one exercise in a single day. 
    
    Could you help Anujay's coaches and find the maximal possible amount of strength that he can gain?
    
    Input Format
    
    The first line of the input contains two space separated integers N and M.  Then there are M lines, each describing a single exercise with the numbers Li Ri Di Ci Sirespectively.
    
    Output Format
    
    Output the maximal possible amount of strength on the first line of output. It is guaranteed that answer will always fit into 32 bit signed int.
    Note: If input DOES NOT match constraints, print ERROR in string format.
    
    Sample Input
    
    5 2
    1 3 5 5 2
    4 5 5 10 1
    
    Sample Output
    
    38
    
    Explanation
    
    Constraints
    1≤N,M≤100000 
    1≤Li≤Ri≤Di≤N 
    1≤Si,Ci≤10000

[2015-09-13T11:57-04:00] Ashwin Kapre: 

    Problem Statement
    
    A contest is organized to find the most attractive city in the world. N cities take part in the contest and they are indexed from 1 to N (from east to west). The jury is unable to explicitly choose the winner, so they decide to do the following: 
    
    K travelers are chosen from the volunteers across the world. Each one of them travels across the world (from east to west) N times. During the ith trip, a traveler visits only those cities whose index is divisible by i. 
    
    Every traveler has one (unique) award at his disposal, and he has one favorite city which he considers as the most beautiful. Let's represent jth traveler's favorite city by mj. During the trip, whenever jth traveler visits his favorite city, mj, one of following things happen:
    
    If the traveler has the award, he gives it to the city.
    If traveler has already given the award, he takes it back. Note that each traveler can give/take only his award.
    After all the K travelers have finished their journey, each city will have a non-negative number of awards. Your task is to print out the indices of cities which have at least one award, and for each such city you should print the number of awards owned by it.
    
    Input Format
    
    In the first line there is one number, N, denoting the number of cities.  In the second line there is one number, K - the number of travelers. Each of the next K lines contains mi - the index of city which the ith traveler considers the most beautiful.
    
    Output Format
    
    If after the process, Y cities have at least 1 award, print Y lines. In each of those lines print two numbers: ci (index of city) and xi (number of awards which ci will have). Print cities in increasing order of their indices.
    
    Sample Input
    
    5
    2
    3
    4
    
    Sample Output
    
    4 1
    
    Explanation
    
    Constraints
    1≤N≤106
    1≤K≤106
    1≤mi≤N,where i∈[1,K]

[2017-04-03T11:37-04:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    Emergency Care System
    Domain:
    System that will handle communication process between registered user facing medical emergency and hospitals.
    Description:
    Medical emergencies are unpredictable and can lead to several after-effects unless handled immediately. Emergency Care system will facilitate communication between all parties involved in handling crisis. This system will provide a way to communicate their requirements easily to hospitals and will enable hospitals to attend to the patient accordingly.
    Scope:
    •    Get notification of medical emergency requests
    •    Maintain records of all hospitals, doctors and pharmacies involved in the ecosystem of one city
    •    Establish communication between all involved parties (i.e. hospital administrators, doctor organizations and request originators) to resolve individual requests
    
    Conclusion:
    Patients and hospitals will get a simple way of communication. This will lead to efficient and quick assistance in case of emergencies by minimizing the time delay in the process.

[2010-08-22T01:27-04:00] Facebook User: 

    Hello everyone....
    
    We are organizing a Photography Competition in Satara... Following are the subjects and clauses... 
    
    The categories are :-
    1. Professional 
    2. Amateur
    3. Mobile
    
    The Topics are :-
    1. Streets of Satara District.
    2. Satara... through my eyes.
    3. Sunrises or Sunsets.
    4. Micro Photography.
    
    All the Photographers are most welcomed to send their photos. An Exhibition will be organized out of the selected photos only. The last day will be a prize distribution day to the winners from each Category.   
    
    Date of Exhibition :-  11th & 12th Sep 2010.
    
    Venue :- New English School, Satara.
    
    Send the photos to address :- 
    Aditya Phadke.
    'Indraprastha',385 C, Laxmi-Narayan colony, shahupuri, Satara.
    415002.
    
    Last Date of submitting the Photos (deadline):- 7th Sep 2010.
    
    Participation fee :- Rs.75/- 
    
    Everybody is allowed to send 3 photographs per Form and only those photos received before the deadline will be taken into consideration.. 
    
    Clauses :- 
    1. The size for Camera photos :- 8 X 12 inches.(Matt prints)
    2. The size for Mobile camera photos :- 5 X 7 inches.(Matt prints)
    3. Send the PHOTO PRINTS along with your name behind every photograph, written with a black permanent marker along with the participation form & fee.
    4. Do not send soft copies.
    5. * All the rights of Usage of the photographs will be restricted to the organizing committee.
    6. The Forms will be available at :-
    
    A. "Swad Evening Spot", near shopping center, near Digvijay automobiles(now Honda showroom), powai naka, satara.
    
    B. "Woods Cafe", near kamani haud, satara.
    
    C. "Add Agencies", opposite Shahu kala mandir, Behind rajwada, satara.
    
    D. For participants outside satara, please download the form from the profile named - Shreyas Deshpande, satara.... 
    
    We are also organizing a photography workshop on the 18th & 19th of sep 2010.
    
    For further details contact :- 
    Avdhoot Kirpekar :- 9762638141.
    Aditya Phadke :- 9096370001 , 9762526426. 
    Shreyas Deshpande :- 9975727527.

    4. nw u & i independantly start thinking wht other might think or wht          other should think..
    5. u should think if numbers were 1 & 2 (as ashwin told us they were natural numbers) wht would happen?...
    6. me(2) would ask u(1) d question  'd u knw my no?' & u say '"yes!" .coz u had '1' ..i also nw know as u said yes at 1st attemt of question dat u have got '1'..

[2012-04-05T01:13-04:00] Kaustubh Jogalekar: 

    ...7. further if they were 3(u) & 2(m) & i would 1st ask d question..
    u say "no"! coz u dnt knw whether mine is 2 or 4...
    
    * count d number f questions askd (overall)
    *also note dat even number asks 1st..
    
    8. den u ask m d question..(remember previously u said 'no')..i guess dat ,as u replied wit 'no' , ur number is not 1.. it is 3!! so i would answer "yes"!!...
    
    9..u were confused initially betn 2 & 4..bt as i answered at 2nd question..my no mst be 2 ..u guess this & at 3rd question(overall)
    & nw as i ask u again u answer "yes"!!!
    
    10. nw generalise dis to ne 2 numbers
        even person asks 1st 
    u/I say "yes"!!! at ur/mine  number of overall question count..!!!
    
    it is dat easy!!!!!!!!....:)
    
    
    hope u read dis completely....khup diwasani itke lihalay..:)

[2012-04-30T10:10-04:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    You are the ruler of a medieval empire and you are about to have a celebration tomorrow. The celebration is the most important party you have ever hosted. You've got 1000 bottles of wine you were planning to open for the celebration, but you find out that one of them is poisoned.
    
    The poison exhibits no symptoms until death. Death occurs within ten to twenty hours after consuming even the minutest amount of poison.
    
    You have over a thousand slaves at your disposal and just under 24 hours to determine which single bottle is poisoned.
    
    You have a handful of prisoners about to be executed, and it would mar your celebration to have anyone else killed.
    
    What is the smallest number of prisoners you must have to drink from the bottles to be absolutely sure to find the poisoned bottle within 24 hours?
    
     	
    hope so tula he puzzle mahit nasel..

[2012-04-30T12:17-04:00] Kaustubh Jogalekar: 

    2^9<1000<2^10  so ans is 10
    every bottle is considered a 10 bit binary no. 1 at some (a th position) position says that prisoner is made to drink. according to combination of died prisoners guess d bottle's no !
    yup i had solved it previously:)  :(

Conversation with Narendra Bokil:

[2017-09-30T07:58-04:00] Narendra Bokil: 

    ✍
    
                  *तुऴजाष्टकम..!!*
    
         मागे म्हटल्याप्रमाणे "आद्य शंकराचार्य विरचित तुलजाष्टक" टाईप करण्याचा योग शेवटी आज जुळुन आला! २६ ऑक्टोबर २००१ च्या 'सकाळ'च्या दसरा विशेष पुरवणीत श्री. वा.ल. मंजूळ यांचा "एक दुर्मिळ हस्त लिखित" असा लेख छापुन आला होता! त्यात त्यांनी म्हटल्या प्रमाणे त्यांना श्री तुळजा भवानी स्तोत्र या ग्रंथाचे लहानसे हस्तलिखित मुंगी-पैठण येथे, श्री कृष्ण दयार्णवांच्या सांप्रदायिक सनातन मठामधे मिळाले. त्या लेखातील काही भागः
    
         आद्य शंकराचार्यांनी तुळजा भवानीची सेव तुळजापुरी गेल्यावर संस्कृत आठ श्लोक रचुन केली आहे. आचार्यांच्या कोणत्याही ग्रंथात या स्तोत्राचा समावेश नाही. तीन पानांच्या या स्तोत्राचे हस्तलिखित १०x १५ सें.मीं आकाराचे आहे. कागद पातळ, पिवळे, जीर्ण आहेत. 'पिपिलीका (मुंगी) नगरे, सनातन गुरु सन्निधौ, गोदावरी तटे' लिहिल्याचा त्यावर उल्लेख आहे. हा मजकूर शके १७९० मधे ( म्हणजे १४१ वर्षांपूर्वी ) नकलून घेतलेला आहे.
    
    *||श्रीमद आद्य शंकराचार्य विरचित तुलजाष्टकम||*
    
    दुग्धेन्दु कुन्दोज्जवलसुंदराङ्गीं
    मुक्ताफलाहार विभूषिताङ्गीम|
    शुभ्राम्बरां स्तनभरालसाङ्गीं
    *वन्देहमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||१||*
    
    बालार्कभासामतिचा रुहासां
    माणिक्य मुक्ताफल हार कण्ठीम|
    रक्तांबरा रक्तविशालनेत्रीं
    *वन्देsहमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||२||*
    
    श्यामाङ्गवर्णां मृगशावनेत्रां
    कौशेवस्त्रां कुसुमेषु पूज्याम|
    कस्तुरिकाचन्दनचर्चितांगी,
    *वन्देSहमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||३||*
    
    पीताम्बरां चम्पक कान्ती गौरीम
    अलङकृतामुत्तममण्डनैश्च|
    नाशाय भूतां भूवि दानवांनां,
    *वन्देSमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||४||*
    
    चन्द्रार्कताटङ्कधरां त्रिनेत्रां
    शूल दधानामतिकालरुपम|
    विपक्षनाशाय धृतायुधां तां,
    *वन्देSहमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||५||*
    
    ब्रम्हेन्द्र नारायणरुद्रपूज्यां
    देवांगनाभि: परिगीयामानाम |
    स्तुतांवचोभिर्मुनिनारदा द्यै:
    *वन्देSहमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||६||*
    
    अष्टांग योगे: सनकादिभिश्च,
    ध्यातां मुनीन्द्रैश्च समाधीगम्याम |
    भक्तस्य नित्यम भूवी कामधेनुं,
    *वन्देSहमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||७||*
    
    सिंहासनस्थां परिवीज्यमानां
    देवै: समस्तैश्च सुचामरैश्च |
    छत्रं दधाना अतिशुभ्रवर्णं
    *वन्देSहमाद्यां तुलजाभवानीम ||८||*
    
    पूर्णः कटाक्षोSखिललोकमातु:
    गिरीन्द्रकन्यां भजतामसुधन्याम |
    दारिद्र्यकं नैव कदा जनानां
    *चिन्ता कुत:स्यात भवसागरस्य ||९||*
    
    तुलजाष्टकमिदं स्तोत्रं
    त्रिकालं यः पठेत नरः |
    आयु: कीर्ति यशो लक्ष्मी
    *धन पुत्रान वाप्नुयात ||१०||*
    
    *इति श्रीमच्छङ्कराचार्या विरचितम तुलजादेवीस्तोत्रं संपूर्णम ||*
    
    *शुभं भवतु, शके १७९०, विभावनाब्दे माघ शुक्ल तृतियाथां भृगुवासरे श्रीमत पिपिलीकाक्षेत्रे, गोदायाम, तटस्थित श्री सनातन सद्गुरुसमाधी सन्निधौ लिखितम ||*
    
    * जय जय तुऴजा भवानी*

Conversation with Paras Bhavarthi, Tejashree Deshmukh-Gadre, Yogesh Bhavarthi:

[2013-08-20T22:21-04:00] Yogesh Bhavarthi: 

    एक दूधवाला महापालिका इस्पितळात शेवटच्या घटका मोजत
    होता. डॉक्टर त्याला वाचवण्याचे प्रयत्न करत होते. जवळ
    त्याची बायको आणि दोन मुले होती.
    दूधवाला त्याना म्हणाला “ मी काही आता जगत नाही.
    माझ्यामागे तुम्ही आपसात भांडू नका. आपल्या घराजवळचे वीस
    वाडे आणि चार चाळी मी बायकोला देतोय.
    ती बंगल्यांची मोठी स्कीम मी मोठ्याला देतोय आणि मेन
    रोडचे तीन ऑफिस टॉवर धाकट्याला ठेवतोय. “ डॉक्टर चाट पडून
    म्हणाले “ याना महापालिका इस्पितळात
    कशाला आणलेत ? तुम्ही तर चांगले श्रीमंत दिसताय !”
    बायको कपाळावर हात मारत म्हणाली “ डोम्बल्याचे श्रीमंत !
    अहो, दूध पोचवायच्या लाइन बद्दल बोलतायत ते...!!!

[2017-07-07T19:05-04:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    Politics[edit]
    United Kingdom[edit]
    In the United Kingdom, if a local or national election has resulted in a tie in which candidates receive exactly the same number of votes after three recounts, the winner can be decided either by drawing straws/lots, coin flipping,[1] or drawing the high card in a pack of cards.[citation needed]
    
    On 5th May 2017, Local election candidates in Northumberland drew straws to decide the winner in South Blythe Ward. Liberal Democrat candidate Lesley Rickerby was declared the winner, denying Conservatives overall control of Northumberland County Council.
    
    USA[edit]
    On 20 November 2015, a Mississippi state election was settled by drawing straws after both candidates received 4,589 votes. This resulted in Blaine Eaton being re-elected to the Mississippi House of Representatives.[2]

[2013-10-07T06:25-04:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    Fairy Tale!!    
    
     He was bored.If it wasn't for detention by prof. Mcgonagall he wouldn't be in library at the first place.He saw girl sitting in quite alone spot.He wouldn't have noticed her if he wasn't scanning so intently.He had charms and transfiguration classes with that Ravenclaw girl in second year.
         He concentrated back at his essay. He was supposed to turn in 2 rolls of parchments on 'how to differentiate object characteristics if it is transfigured from 2 different items' and he had large stack of books in front of him.
    His eyes wandered at her direction again.Something was different in her appearance than before.But he couldn't point out.He stared at her intently trying to catch what he had missed.She must be completing some homework because parchments and quills laid on her table almost forgotten.She was playing with her long red curls as she read thick book in her hand.She sighed as she flipped page and placed her palm under her chin.He knew being engrossed in real good book though he wasn't much of reader.He wondered which book she was reading with such interest.
         He studied her the way painter studies portrait.He noticed how her long red curls were slowly changing into long honey blond waves.He was fascinated to find metamorphmagus. He had heard the tales but never seen it in action before.
         She went on reading her book and he went on studying her from distance.He saw how her hair color changed from honey blonde to red to orange to chocolate brown to black as she read book intently.He was fascinated. He got up and went straight to her table.
    He tapped slightly to inform her about his presence.She looked up from book little dizzily. As if he had dragged her in library from another world.He smiled a little when he saw her startled to find him sitting besides her."Pardon me.I was little preoccupied"she said.
    "that would be understatement"he replied pointing towards glass so that she could see her multicolored hair.She smiled coy smile of embarrassment.
    "Still better than accidentally changing into elf ears"she murmured.
    "What held your attention so much???" he asked trying to be prince charming.
    "Its fairy tales of muggles. I have an essay due about magic world references in it.And its so interesting that I got caught up in it." she cut short her babbling as she realized whom he was talking with.No one should day things like that in front of Slytherin prince.
    He chuckled."Any luck so far??Muggles are the most ignorant people ever lived on the earth.Worse than mudbloods."
    She flinched a little at 'mudblood'.Something sparkled in her now green eyes."There is magic world reference in every story.But sadly wizards and witches are not always good."
    "Like muggles deserves being good to them."
    "16 year old damsels don't deserve being under Draught of living death either."
    "There had to be.How else knights and princes would enter??"He smirked.
    "That can be arranged without villains. Help maiden to reach her prince."she debated.
    She told him many stories to prove her point.He wasn't actually listening to them.He was too busy in staring her changing appearance as she talked.
    "So basically there is always a prince charming in story??"He asked ,hoping to stop her talking.
    "Ohh no.Not always.Some times there is mean arrogant scary wizard who had locked himself up.I am guessing that would be being animagus went horribly wrong." She remarked without looking up.
    "And a damsel in distress always  beautiful beyond words?"She blushed when she realized he was talking about her.
    "then they will meet.May be in ballroom or in castle or in forest" she spoke in her sweet voice.
    "Or in library and may be prince softened a little because of her presence " he suggested.Her face was brighter shade of red and her now blue eyes danced.
    "Then may be he would ask her for a dance"she whispered playfully ,holding his stare for the first time.
    Both of them flicked their wand.He moved table out of way and she adjusted ambiance.
    Both of them danced without music for a while.
    "And then there is magical kiss" He beamed as he leaned in.
    She tiptoed and brushed her lips to his.
    "just as perfect as this" 
    He hold her by her waist pulling her towards him and she didn't protest.
    A bell ;last warning for students to return in their common rooms; echoed.She shuddered as if snapping out of some kind of enchantment.She freed herself from his hold and ran towards library door.She hesitated for a second and glanced back at him.He stared deeply into her eyes which mirrored his own grey but they weren't icy as his.He almost ran to stop her but she ran away, leaving him alone like prince in story she had told before.

[2012-06-29T09:51-04:00] Vishal Falake: 

    Your percentile score = { (No, of people who got less than you/ equal to you) / (no. of people appearing in the exam) } x 100
    
    Thus, if in an exam, 10 people give the test and 9 people get either less than what you got or equal to what you got, your percentile score is:
    
    {9/10} x 100 = 90 percentile.

[2012-01-05T14:26-05:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    Do not believe about the rumors about "Smith Sisters Murdered Anonymously".. Why?
    
    Here is why.
    
    The younger sister is murdered while the older girl is either sleeping beside or going to the window to check on an odd sound, yet the older sibling hears nothing happening in the room and is alerted to something's being amiss only because the bed is wet and ill-smelling upon her return to it. 
    
    Rather than scream for help or run from the room, the older girl hides in the closet. 
    
    The older sister is pulled from the closet by her murderer and her body is returned there to be hung for her parents to discover, yet while she's in this closed space before her killer takes her from it, she carves hers and her sister's names and the time and date. If she had something with which to gouge messages into the floorboards or onto the walls, why didn't she use it to stab at her attacker and escape his clutches? Also, wasn't it thoughtful of her murderer to afford her time to finish her woodworking escapades before coming for her? 
    
    The parents (who we presume are sleeping in the same house, since the story doesn't mention their being absent that night) hear nothing of their two daughters being murdered. 
    
    The son (who we work out from the story is 12 years old: "15 years ago" less "2 years after the the sisters deaths" less a nine-month gestation period) lives those twelve years in the murder room yet never once notices the message carved in the closet. 
    
    The girls were murdered "In 1993" yet the IM'ing ghost of one of them informs her brother she died "15 years ago." Our calendar says it's 2005, not 2008. 
    
    Instant message capability didn't become an online reality until 1997 when AOL introduced its Instant Messenger service. Yahoo Messenger (which the narrative tells us was used by the murderer to contact one of the sisters prior to his killing her) began in 1999. However, while IM didn't exist in 1993, chat rooms did — IRC (Internet Relay Chat) was most certainly part of the cyber world at least as far back as 1993, else I retain rather vivid yet baseless false memories of what I was doing with a great many of my nights back then.

[2012-01-05T14:26-05:00] Anuja Kapre: 

    do not believe..
    stop imagining :-):-D

    After reaching in class..
    Peeping thr half closed door and looking for any1 from group..
    Once one of them is found remove headphones check if cell is on silent mode..
    "ma'am..."
    Stepping in the class n go where grp is sitting..
    Greeting everyone..
    "hey hiee" "hey looking nyc" "y didnt u reply yesterde??" "i need to tell you story.. After lect!!"
    Open book n search for blank pages..
    Search for pen in bag..
    Checking cell for new msg..
    Reading msg..
    Replying n texting everyone good morning..
    Look at teacher..
    If he has written anything on board copying it down ask benchmate.. "wt he has written???i havnt understood a word..he cant even teach!!!"
    Pattern goes till attendance..
    Disturbing frndz wen der rollcall is near..
    Chitchatting till nxt teacher comes...
    Again same thing repeats for every lecture with occasional chalk fights or water fights and scribbling on each others notebooks or some time on bench we r seeting on :P
    In real boring lecture searching for sketches over net dat changu can draw in her book..
    or having conversation with troll pics as smileys :P (remember MVK ka wo ML wala lect neha????)
    Or writing nonsense things in eachothers notebooks(u should read Chinky's notebook where apurv has written all things he could catch her talking wen we wanted to reschedule our lectures)
    And not but not least all pages checked by chinky with her autograph on it..
    
    playing games or chitchatting over phone never gets old.We have to disturb anyone who is paying attention in d class..
    how can i forget nidhi kohli eating wadapav in lecture without giving me a bite or Ashish Birajdar playing various pranks :@
    Ashish anyone would hav beaten u up for throwing thier cell away.. :P :@
    and everyday we need to rush to class after break so that we can sit on 4th bench onwards.. :D :D
    even good galz in our class r spoiled..:O
    sonti aditi shreya ishani not fair!! :P :PU were official first benchers.. :D 
    well nidhi baheti and pranjali etc are not dat spoiled yet :D :D
    and everyone copying assingments as if they are xerox machines dats d epic moment of the class :D :D everyone is writing with all their might and pages of assingment are being passed..
    Practical sessions is different story!! I had never thought enggineering practicals will include singing songs and poems :P :P Or everyone just sitting on one PC as group for entire practical and playing quizzes :D HAts off to Apurv n sujata who sang nursary rhymes and balgeete n all poems we had in our school syallabus.. n only our batch can tell how we tolerated dem.. :D 
    I dunnoo what I had expected abt H div!!!bUT definately not this..
    not a class playing water/chalk/paper-ball fights :P
    not d class celebrating birthdays with weird unpredictable gifts :P
    not d class dat bunks feedback :P
    
    I cant believe my colleges r almost over..
    I wont sit in dat 1301 class again and attend any lecture..
    no practical or tutorial sessions..
    no more checking for attendence n calculating marks required for passing..
    no more assingments (gosh what wud i do in my spared time)
    
    All these years passed by so fast and feels like we walked in here just few days ago. I just dunno where did d time go???
    all dsa practs we bunked and all DELD lecture we were on DONT CARE mode..
    i dunno wen we reached in third year and counted "UMMM" in SP lecture..
    or all bouncer DAA lectures!!
    All the placement era!!
    where all friendz were with me being screwed by interview process or were there for me!!
    And STQA lecture with all Johnsance English (Thank god i didnt witness dat :P ) or DSP lecture where we all went in HYPER MODE..
    where did d time go? 
    Today only thing running in my mind is how to say goodbye to this town,this college,this class where we spent all these four years racing for this day, where we made our best friends who will be there for us for rest of
